Interface IExecutable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ICascader, IPerformsRecurringTask
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseAutoStartableComponent, BaseAutoStartableComponentPerformingRecurringTask, BaseExecutableComponent, BaseExecutableComponentPerformingRecurringTask, Cascader, JMXWatcher, TLSCapableJMXConnectorServer

    public interface IExecutable
    This interface is implemented by components which can be started and stopped.
    Author:
    Guillaume Jacob (guillaume.jacob@orcsoftware.com)

    • Method Detail

      • start

        void start()
    throws ExecutableStartException,
           IllegalStateException
        Starts this executable component.
        Throws:
        ExecutableStartException - if an error occurred which prevented the executable component from starting
        IllegalStateException - if either of the following occurs:
        • the component's initialization state is not InitializationState.INITIALIZED
        • the component's execution state is not ExecutionState.STOPPED

      • stop

        void stop()
   throws IllegalStateException
        Stops this executable component.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if either of the following occurs:
        • the component's initialization state is not InitializationState.INITIALIZED
        • the component's execution state is not ExecutionState.RUNNING

      • getExecutionState

        ExecutionState getExecutionState()
        Returns this executable component's execution state.
        Returns:
        a ExecutionState
